-- Australia Reaches 208-5 on Opening Day of Second Cricket Test
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2012-04-15T22:49:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-15/australia-reaches-208-5-on-opening-day-of-second-cricket-test.html
Australia  reached 208-5 on day one
of the second cricket Test against West Indies after winning the
toss on a slow pitch in Port of Spain, Trinidad.  Shane Watson top scored with 56 off 172 balls, while
captain Michael Clarke made 45.  Mike Hussey  was 26 not out at
stumps, with Matthew Wade on 11.  West Indies off-spinner Shane Shillingford, playing his
first Test since November 2010, took two wickets for 56 runs
from his 32 overs. Fast bowler Kemar Roach also took two
wickets.  Australia, which won the first Test in Barbados by three
wickets, picked two specialist spin bowlers with Michael Beer
coming in to partner Nathan Lyon. The final match in Dominica
starts April 23.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  